title: Shrimp Scampi
summary: Shrimp Scampi requires around 7 minutes from start to finish. This recipe serves 2 and costs $22.44 per serving. One serving contains 3232 calories, 216g of protein, and 119g of fat. A couple people made this recipe, and 40 would say it hit the spot. This recipe is typical of Mediterranean cuisine. If you have oh! and don't forget the garlic, garlic, pepper, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. To use up the olive oil you could follow this main course with the Sauteed Banana, Granolan and Yogurt Parfait as a dessert. It works well as a main course. It is brought to you by How Sweet Eats. Taking all factors into account, this recipe earns a spoonacular score of 91%, which is super. Similar recipes are Shrimp 2 Ways: Soy Sauce-Grilled Shrimp with Spinach Salad and New-Style Scampi, Shrimp Scampi, and Shrimp Scampi.

winePairing.pairingText: Pinot Grigio, Riesling, and Sauvignon Blanc are great choices for Shrimp. These crisp white wines work well with shrimp prepared in a variety of ways, whether grilled, fried, or in garlic sauce. You could try Proverb Pinot Grigio Wine. Reviewers quite like it with a 5 out of 5 star rating and a price of about 13 dollars per bottle.
